    {
      "kind": "guardrails",
      "reason": "RCM-FR-110 policies (HIPAA baseline, CMS LCD/NCD/NCCI billing edits, No Surprises Act balance-billing, state balance-billing configs, TILA/FDCPA payment-plan disclosures, RAC/MAC audit posture) require guardrail-service / OPA materialization, which Core does not expose as a pack surface yet. Proposal-mode + four-eyes approval in agent-runtime already satisfies the human-review guarantee (BRD 26 BR-1) for every pack-configured agent."
    },
    {
      "kind": "agent_recipes",
      "reason": "RCM-FR-030..080 bespoke LangGraph recipes (coding_copilot, denial_response, underpayment_detector, ar_prioritizer, patient_collections, coding_audit_prep) require agent-runtime graph-module registration (BRD 23 BR-12). This pack specializes the existing case-triage + analytics agents via TenantAgentConfig prompt_params + tenant-scope RAG grounding instead; all writes remain proposal-mode per BR-1 (RCM_AUTONOMOUS_BILLING_FORBIDDEN)."
    },
    {
      "kind": "connection_templates",
      "reason": "RCM-FR-090 read connectors (Epic Resolute FHIR/HL7v2, Athenahealth Collector, eCW, NextGen, Cerner Millennium, EDI 837/835/276/277/275, Waystar, Change Healthcare, Availity) require customer credentials and pack-service connector materialization. The pack ships seed datasets in the exact landing shape (837 claims, 835 remit lines, denials, A/R aging); production connectors are configured through Data > Connections."
    },
    {
      "kind": "write_adapters",
      "reason": "RCM-FR-090 write adapters (Epic charge/claim/note, Athena/eCW/Cerner claim update, Waystar/Availity submission, outbound EDI 837 corrected claim + EDI 276 status inquiry) execute only behind pack-service's materialization contract and customer credentials; per BRD 26 BR-1 the coding-write adapter refuses without a signed grant and all platform-side writes remain proposal-mode."
    },
    {
      "kind": "eval_sets",
